**Explanation:**
Let the monthly income be \( I \). Over 10 months, the labourer spent \( 10 \times 85 = 850 \), incurring a debt of \( 10I - 850 \). In the next 4 months, spending \( 4 \times 60 = 240 \), he earned \( 4I \), cleared the debt, and saved 30. Solving \( 4I - 240 = (10I - 850) + 30 \) gives \( I = 180 \).
